title.narrative: Integrated approach towards malaria elimination in foci 1A, 1B and 1C

description.narrative: Guyana - Malaria - Ministry of Health of the Co-operative Republic of Guyana - MOH. This program has the following goals: To reduce overall malaria burden by at least 75% by 2025 relative to 2015.. To facilitate elimination of local P. falciparum transmission of by 2025.. The objectives of this program are: To reinforce coordination of all malaria activities with Regional Health Departments and stakeholders. To reinforce malaria surveillance, data management, and monitoring and evaluation (M&E). To reinforce malaria diagnosis and treatment among high-risk and vulnerable populations. To guarantee access and optimize use of LLINs through Social Behaviour Change CommunicationIEC
